snippet: Hundreds of police moved into downtown Hong Kong on Tuesday morning, pushing back pro-democracy protesters who overnight had erected barricades around their main street camp.
abstract: Hundreds of police move into downtown Hong Kong, pushing back pro-democracy protesters who had erected barricades overnight around their main street camp.

byline.original: By CHRIS BUCKLEY and MICHAEL FORSYTHE
byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Alan Wong, Keith Bradsher, Neil Gough, Laurence Tan and Siobhan Downes.

lead_paragraph: Hundreds of police moved into downtown Hong Kong on Tuesday morning, pushing back pro-democracy protesters who overnight had erected barricades around their main street camp.

headline.main: Hong Kong Police Remove Barriers and Protesters’ Encampments
headline.print_headline: Hong Kong Protesters Reinforce Barriers After Rivals Try to Demolish Them
